subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. 

Agrotis robusta

differs from other South American species of 

Agrotis

by the following combination of characters: 
1
) male forewing ground color light brown and female grayish brown; 
2
) patagium and tegulum darker than thorax; 
3
) subterminal line light brown, extending basally between M 
1
–M 
2
–M 
3
veins seeming two basally black and light brown-tipped arrows; 
4
) in male genitalia vesica with basal spined band absent; 
5
) in female genitalia corpus bursae with two signa; and 
6
) appendix bursae 
4–5
× as long as corpus bursae.
